Bug.WithStack:
We should have path/variable entry substitution support 
in the core as a service.

Basically the code in Eclipse/Debug/Core can serve as the model
and probably could be reuse entirely.
After meeting with vlad, I can handle this.
Although the scanner discovery may be need this, it is not dependent.
Vlad the part one is done.

Take a look at classes:
 IPathEntryVariableManager
 IPathEntryVariableChangeListener
 PathEntryVariableChangeEvent

To use:
{
  IPathEntryVariableManager manager = 
    CCorePlugin.getDefault.getPathEntryVariableManger();
  
  manager.setValue("HOME", "/home/vlad");

  // returns "BIN_HOME=${HOME}/bin" --> "BIN_HOME=/home/vlad/bin"
  String expanded = manager.resolve("BIN_HOME=${HOME}/bin");

}

A change to the interface IPath was use instead of String

To use:
{
  IPathEntryVariableManager manager = 
    CCorePlugin.getDefault.getPathEntryVariableManger();
  
  manager.setValue("HOME", new Path("/home/vlad"));

  // returns "${HOME}/bin" --> "/home/vlad/bin"
  IPath expanded = manager.resolve("${HOME}/bin");

}

Implemented in the head and enable with UI in the preference page.

