Bug.WithStack:
The problem is as follows:

Thumbnail is listening (via UpdateListener) an UpdateManager and handles
notifyPainting event. If the thumbnail's source figure is about to be painted,
the thumbnail asks for repainting:

(class Thumbnail)
public void notifyPainting(Rectangle damage, Map dirtyRegions) {
	Iterator dirtyFigures = dirtyRegions.keySet().iterator();
	while (dirtyFigures.hasNext()) {
		IFigure current = (IFigure)dirtyFigures.next();
		while (current != null) {
			if (current == getSource()) {
				setDirty(true);
				repaint();
				return;
			}
			current = current.getParent();
		}
	}
}

The repaint() method causes the UpdateManager to add a dirty region:

(class Figure)
public void repaint(int x, int y, int w, int h) {
	if (isVisible())
		getUpdateManager().addDirtyRegion(this, x, y, w, h);
}

And now we come to a point where the implementation of DeferredUpdateManager is
important:

(a piece of code from a class DeferredUpdateManager)
protected void repairDamage() {

	...

	if (!dirtyRegions.isEmpty()) {
		firePainting(damage, dirtyRegions);
		dirtyRegions.clear();
	}

	...	
}

We can see that the code flow is as follows:

0. something changed in the thumbnail's source figure
1. repairDamage is called (DeferredUpdateManager)
2. firePainting is called (DeferredUpdateManager)
	2.1. notifyPainting is called (Thumbnail)
	2.2. repaint is called (Figure)
	2.3. addDirtyRegion is called (DeferredUpdateManager) - this add an item in
dirtyRegiods field
6. a statement dirtyRegions.clear() is executed

We can see that even if the thumbnail asks for repainting, the information is
lost, because dirtyRegions field
is cleared.

The path proposal will be in the following bugzilla comment.
My proposal is to replace a piece of code:

(a piece of code from a class DeferredUpdateManager)
protected void repairDamage() {

	...

	if (!dirtyRegions.isEmpty()) {
		firePainting(damage, dirtyRegions);
		dirtyRegions.clear();
	}

	...	
}

By this code:

protected void repairDamage() {

	...

	if (!dirtyRegions.isEmpty()) {
		Map copy = new HashMap(dirtyRegions);
		dirtyRegions.clear();
		firePainting(damage, copy);
	}

	...	
}

