protected void repairDamage() {

	...

	if (!dirtyRegions.isEmpty()) {
		Map backup = dirtyRegions;
		dirtyRegions = new HashMap();
		firePainting(damage, backup);
	}

	...	
}
Thumbnail is intended to be used in a separate LightweightSystem from the 
source figure.  Are you using it in this way?
I am using it in the same LightweightSystem.

(My editor consists of three columns, each has its own small thumbnail used for
scrolling the column.)
Fixed as follows:

if (!dirtyRegions.isEmpty()) {
	Map oldRegions = dirtyRegions;		
	dirtyRegions = new HashMap();
	firePainting(damage, oldRegions);
}

Of course, you now have the problem that you thumbnail will infinitely repaint
over and over because it sees itself painting and decides to repaint.
Randy, make sure you add Milos Volauf as a contributor to the copyright.
This is an obvious programming fix in this case. I wrote comment 7 without 
having seen comment 4. We do the same thing in lots of other places.
